\title{Taylor polynomial}
\date{2025-05-26}
\taxon{Definition}


\p{A Taylor polynomial of a function #{f} is a polynomial that approximates the function around a specific point. For a function #{f} that is #{n} times differentiable at a point #{a}, the Taylor polynomial of degree #{n} is:}

##{P_n(x) = \sum_{k=0}^{n} \frac{f^{(k)}(a)}{k!}(x-a)^k}
